                            <comment id="94709" author="liang" created="Tue, 23 Sep 2014 13:04:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Chris, patch is here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/12018&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/12018&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="92771" author="liwei" created="Fri, 29 Aug 2014 01:16:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris, yes, that&apos;s exactly what I saw.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="92744" author="hornc" created="Thu, 28 Aug 2014 19:54:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When client re-sends a request, the server will drop it if it is already in progress. Client then is measuring the service time from the sent time of the resend, while the server will report service time of original request. This may be the cause of the disparity.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
